{"word": "skeptic", "definitions": "(n.) a person inclined to question or doubt all accepted opinions (e.g. How does he gain by fortressing himself and his administration away from critics, ..... , and questioners?)<br/>---<br/>(n.) an ancient or modern philosopher who denies the possibility of knowledge, or even rational belief, in some sphere (e.g. Xenophanes was a sceptic who denied that knowledge could be obtained by us humans; at best we merely have beliefs, the truth or falsity of which will remain largely unknown to us.)", "persian": "شکاک است", "synonyms": "cynic, doubter, pessimist, prophet of doom"}